{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.17",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 17,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 17 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:1",
      "text": "God created man of the earth, and made him after his own image.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:2",
      "text": "And he turned him into it again, and clothed him with strength according to himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:3",
      "text": "He gave him the number of his days and time, and gave him power over all things that are upon the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:4",
      "text": "He put the fear of him upon all flesh, and he had dominion over beasts and fowls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:5",
      "text": "He created of him a helpmate like to himself, he gave them counsel, and a tongue, and eyes, and ears, and a heart to devise: and he filled them with the knowledge of understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:6",
      "text": "He created in them the science of the spirit, he fired their heart with wisdom, and shewed them both good and evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:7",
      "text": "He set his eye upon their hearts to shew them the greatness of his works:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:8",
      "text": "That they might praise the name which he hath sanctified: and glory in his wondrous act that they might declare the glorious things of his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:9",
      "text": "Moreover he gave them instructions, and the law of life for an inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:10",
      "text": "He made an everlasting covenant with them, and he shewed them his justice and judgments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:11",
      "text": "And their eye saw the majesty of his glory, and their ears heard his glorious voice, and he said to them: Beware of all iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:12",
      "text": "And he gave to every one of them commandment concerning his neighbour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:13",
      "text": "Their ways are always before him, they are not hidden from his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:14",
      "text": "Over every nation he set a ruler.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:15",
      "text": "And Israel was made the manifest portion of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:16",
      "text": "And all their works are as the sun in the sight of God: and his eyes are continually upon their ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:17",
      "text": "Their covenants were not hid by their iniquity, and all their iniquities are in the sight of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:18",
      "text": "The alms of a man is as a signet with him, and shall preserve the grace of a man as the apple of the eye:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:19",
      "text": "And afterward he shall rise up, and shall render them their reward, to every one upon their own head, and shall turn them down into the bowels of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:20",
      "text": "But to the penitent he hath given the way of justice, and he hath strengthened them that were fainting in patience, and hath appointed to them the lot of truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:21",
      "text": "Turn to the Lord, and forsake thy sins:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:22",
      "text": "Make thy prayer before the face of the Lord, and offend less.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:23",
      "text": "Return to the Lord, and turn away from thy injustice, and greatly hate abomination.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:24",
      "text": "And know the justices and judgments of God, and stand firm in the lot set before thee, and in prayer to the most high God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:25",
      "text": "Go to the side of the holy age, with them that live and give praise to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:26",
      "text": "Tarry not in the error of the ungodly, give glory before death. Praise perisheth from the dead as nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:27",
      "text": "Give thanks whilst thou art living, whilst thou art alive and in health thou shalt give thanks, and shalt praise God, and shalt glory in his mercies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:28",
      "text": "How great is the mercy of the Lord, and his forgiveness to them that turn to him!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:29",
      "text": "For all things cannot be in men, because the son of man is not immortal, and they are delighted with the vanity of evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:30",
      "text": "What is brighter than the sun; yet it shall be eclipsed. Or what is more wicked than that which flesh and blood hath invented? and this shall be reproved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.17.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 17,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 17:31",
      "text": "He beholdeth the power of the height of heaven: and all men are earth and ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
